About this hotel

On a bustling street surrounded by eateries, this relaxed hotel is 3 km from both the closest public beach and Tanger Ville railway station. It's a 12-minute walk from the Grand Socco, a lively plaza with an open-air market.

    Kenneth Tangerois3 Maroc2 years ago on Google
    4/5
    Hotel Chellah has been around for at least 50 years, and it has a pleasant, spacious garden where during the warmer summer months lunches are served by the large swimming pool. …
    Hotel Chellah has been around for at least 50 years, and it has a pleasant, spacious garden where during the warmer summer months lunches are served by the large swimming pool.
    The hotel may seem like a throwback to the 1960s or 1970s, but it does have modern conveniences you would expect such as plenty of hot water, comfortable beds and free breakfasts.
    The WiFi works in the reception area but is not reliable in the rest of the hotel's floors and rooms, garden and pool areas. This problem should be fixed.
    The Chellah used to cater to budget-minded English tourists but nowadays it has a mixed crowd from various other countries.
    Sadly, the Chellah Beach Club Restaurant with its on-the-beach gardens where excellent lunches and dinners were served no longer exists. This is because the beachfront was completely sanitized and no more beach restaurants, bars, cabanas and discos remain.
    What now exists is a plain unappealing city beach that no one goes to except near Malabata, and it is dangerous and almost impossible to cross a new six-lane highway to get to the beach since there is no stop light or safe crossing anywhere and you will not see one traffic policeman. Tourists have been killed and maimed by speeding cars while trying to cross the road (Avenue Mohammed VI or Corniche) to get to the beach or other businesses. The city planners do not think about safety of the people and tourists, only about nonstop autoroutes for speeding cars, even in residential areas.
    The unlicensed guardians who collect a few dirhams to park your car, often directly on a torn up sidewalk, create a nightmare for pedestrians trying to squeeze through parked cars. They even park cars on the corners. In any other major city these cars would be towed away and police would issue a ticket and fine.
    Hotel Chellah is conveniently located in downtown Tangier. It is a good alternative to higher priced hotels so you'll have more money to spend on eating out in restaurants and for buying souvenirs of your stay in Morocco.
    This hotel is a good budget alternative to those who do not wish to stay at a cheap pension in the Medina or more expensive hotels.

    About this hotel

    On a bustling street surrounded by eateries, this relaxed hotel is 3 km from both the closest public beach and Tanger Ville railway station. It's a 12-minute walk from the Grand Socco, a lively plaza with an open-air market. …

    Unfussy rooms provide free Wi-Fi, flat-screens and minifridges. Upgraded rooms have balconies; some rooms offer distinct touches such as painted furnishings, stained glass lamps, and/or bathrooms with colorful tiles. Genteel suites add separate living rooms.

    A restaurant with carved wood ceilings features a terrace. There's also a warm lounge and a bar, a garden, and an outdoor pool with a palm tree-shaded sundeck.
